text:
Okay...

I watched the whole thing, headphones on, preconceptions at the door, 'why not' attidude but i just...can't

No disrespect to you ladies for doing this but it does absolutely nothing for me.

I find ASMR odd to begin with but this whole thing just felt silly, the cafe, the cat maids, the RP, i cant take it 'seriously', im just expecting a punchline that never came (likely in part because Gura is involved haha). 
I genuinely laughted to myself when they passed me the drink because i knew they were about to do the thing!

It's that divided feeling where you're amused but saying to yourself "what am I ACTUALLY doing right now!" It's such a bizzare format for me and again I will stress that it's ANY ASMR that i feel that way abkut, not this one specifically

More power to those of ya that enjoy it, i'll bow out knowing I atleast gave it an honest go. My ears are wedlocked to Heavy Metal, you'll find me there in the future haha!

Keep swimmin sharky!

text:
I have, all sorts of mixed and conflicted thoughts on it. Audio balance for one is a mess; but it's fine. Gura is either to quiet or Fauna to loud. Take your pick, it is listenable but distracting. Second is the animation. It looks great! Love the art and bounce and it'd be awesome to have and use as a background or something... But for the ASMR it was trying to it. It is very bouncy. Maybe to much so? But then again I normally only watch in person ASMR like Tingting and Ppomo. So slower movement is nicer. At least for me.

But all that aside, it is very good and well done. Though, I wonder who is doing the actual ASMR audio. Unless they are in the same room together, which I doubt. Having proper 3D audio means a new track, so they have at least three tracks. Oh well~ Still really well done and fun listen!
